\begin_layout Standard
The YTM can be considered as the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

spot rate
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 for the whole period.
 The idea of the YTM is that money is reinvested at the same rate in each
 period.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The sensitivity of the current value of the bond is negatively correlated
 to the coupon rate.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A conversion between bond-equivalent basis and YTM accounts for compounding
 intervals (1 or 2 times a year).
 The YTM is higher than the bond-equivalent basis.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The discount rate is usually the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
